  "ComponentID": "RX8010SJ",
  "ComponentType": "Real-Time Clock (RTC) Module with Integrated Crystal and I²C Interface",
  "Description": "The RX8010SJ is a low-power real-time clock module that integrates a frequency-adjusted 32.768 kHz crystal unit. It provides a full calendar (year, month, day, weekday, hour, minute, second), alarm, timer, and frequency output functions. Communication is handled via a 400 kHz I²C interface. It features ultra-low backup current for battery-powered applications and includes 128 bits of user SRAM.",
